clinical_study.brief_title: Safety, Tolerability, Pharmacokinetics and Pharmacodynamics of TNM002 in Healthy Adults
clinical_study.official_title: A Randomized, Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled, Dose-Escalation Phase I Study to Evaluate the Safety, Tolerability, Pharmacokinetics and Pharmacodynamics Following Intramuscular Administration of a Single Dose of TNM002 in Healthy Subjects

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to evaluate the safety, tolerability, pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics properties of TNM002 following a single intramuscular dose in healthy adult subjects.

detailed_description.textblock: The study a randomized, double-blinded, placebo-controlled, dose-escalation phase I trial. A total of 32 healthy adult subjects will be enrolled into 4 cohorts sequentially. Each participant will receive a single IM dose of TNM002 or placebo according to the cohort in which they were enrolled. After injection (Day 1), participants remain in the study site for observation up to 5 days. Following completion of the safety assessments and sampling for PK/PD analyses on Day 4, participants will be discharged from the study site. On Day 8, 15, 29, 43, 64 and 85, participants will return for safety assessments.

arm_group.description: Sentinel dosing will be conducted for Cohort 1. Two participants will be dosed (1 with TNM002, 1 with placebo) at least 72 hours prior to subsequent dosing. The remaining participants will only be dosed if no significant safety signals are identified in the sentinel participants. In total, eight subjects will be randomly assigned to receive either TNM002 or placebo at a 3:1 ratio (i.e. 6 subjects receive TNM002 and 2 with placebo).
